  "uuid": "dc49cf8dafa6a85890c8b0c5c7a4b68a",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales/Operations Assistant Manager",
  "description": "<h3>Key Responsibilities</h3><h3>Sales & Business Development</h3><ul><li><p>Support sales activities including proposal preparation, costing, quotations, and tender submissions</p></li><li><p>Assist in managing key customer accounts and maintaining strong client relationships</p></li><li><p>Participate in client meetings, site surveys, tastings, and presentations</p></li><li><p>Follow up on sales leads, renewals, and contract extensions</p></li><li><p>Coordinate internally to ensure customer requirements are accurately communicated and delivered</p></li></ul><h3>Operations & Service Delivery</h3><ul><li><p>Support planning and execution of catering operations (events, institutional, or contract catering)</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with central kitchen, logistics, stewarding, and service teams to ensure smooth delivery</p></li><li><p>Monitor service quality, food presentation, and operational standards during events or daily operations</p></li><li><p>Assist in troubleshooting operational issues and implementing corrective actions</p></li></ul><h3>Food Safety & Compliance</h3><ul><li><p>Ensure compliance with food safety, hygiene, and regulatory requirements (e.g. SFA, Halal, client audits)</p></li><li><p>Support internal audits, inspections, and documentation</p></li><li><p>Reinforce SOPs, hygiene standards, and workplace safety practices</p></li></ul><h3>People & Team Support</h3><ul><li><p>Assist in manpower planning, rostering, and deployment</p></li><li><p>Support staff training, coaching, and performance monitoring</p></li><li><p>Promote teamwork, discipline, and service excellence culture</p></li></ul><h3>Administration & Reporting</h3><ul><li><p>Prepare operational and sales reports for management review</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate records for contracts, client correspondence, and SOP documentation</p></li><li><p>Coordinate across departments to ensure timely follow-up and execution</p></li></ul>",
